@startuml
title Sequence Diagram: File Download (with Fault Tolerance)

actor Client
participant "Metadata Server\n(Master)" as Master
participant "Storage Node A\n(Offline/Crashed)" as SN_A
participant "Storage Node B\n(Replica)" as SN_B

== 1. Metadata Query ==
Client -> Master: Request Download (Filename, Auth Token)
activate Master
Master -> Master: Validate Token & Check Permissions
Master -> Master: Lookup FileID and Chunk Locations
Master --> Client: 200 OK (List of Chunks & Node IPs: A, B, C)
deactivate Master

== 2. Fault Tolerant Data Retrieval ==
note over Client, SN_A: Client tries the first Node on the list
Client -> SN_A: TCP connect (Request Chunk 1)
activate SN_A
note over SN_A: Node is offline or network is down!
SN_A --X Client: Connection Timeout / Error
deactivate SN_A

note over Client: Client detects failure,\nmoves to next replica in list
Client -> SN_B: TCP connect (Request Chunk 1)
activate SN_B
SN_B --> Client: Send Chunk 1 Data (TCP Binary Stream)
deactivate SN_B

note over Client: Client successfully receives\ndata and reassembles the file.

@enduml
